column23:
*Background*

To reflect what identity is currently authenticated we show the assigned avatar picture in the masthead. Post UID removal as IDP, user will need to be able to assign avatars on different IDS identity linked to UID. So we will introduce such ability in SAM. 

Current intention is that SAP Profile APIs will be extended so that it can support IDS account avatars (to be done by the community team). SAM will consume those APIs so that users can maintain their IDS account avatars

*Technical Details*
 * Support community team with any UID/IDS related questions and design discussions
 * Investigate and document:
 ** Authentication approach for both scenarios 1) SAM to Avatar to Profile APIs and 2) Account Switcher to Profile APIs
 ** Generating a link on SAM side that navigate the user directly to Edit Profile Picture in profile.sap.com (UIDX-4958)
 ** Endpoints that need to be called from SAM to upload/edit/delete IDS account avatars (UIDX-4705)

 

 

{color:#c1c7d0}*Technical Details*{color}
 * {color:#c1c7d0}define security approach for Read operations (how applications will connect and fetch the avatar from the new API we will create){color}
 ** {color:#c1c7d0}Custom algorithm called from applications on the FE (similar to what SAP Community team introduce for their Avatar API: id + custom logic + hashing){color}
 ** {color:#c1c7d0}Backend to Backend using CTS - note this will require more work for app to integrate with{color}
 ** {color:#c1c7d0}another option (?){color}
 * {color:#c1c7d0}define storage approach - Azure Blob storage vs Mongo DB vs other options{color}
 * {color:#c1c7d0}define approach on how do we force/validate the aspect ratio 1:1 and how do we resize - what library to use, etc.{color}

 

{color:#c1c7d0}*Success Criteria*{color}
 * {color:#c1c7d0}Storage approach defined and agreed{color}
 * {color:#c1c7d0}Security approach defined and agreed{color}
